    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "If you look at build logs for `[update workspace, new required, mutable parameter added]` test, you will notice that requests:\r\n\r\n```\r\n2023-08-31T08:13:48.2380836Z [stdout] [update workspace, new required, mutable parameter added]: [onRequest] method=GET url=http://localhost:3000/api/v2/templateversions/00597065-da01-40ef-8720-31efd34c7e61 postData=\r\n\r\n2023-08-31T08:14:15.3718556Z [stdout] [update workspace, new required, mutable parameter added]: [onRequest] method=GET url=http://localhost:3000/api/v2/deployment/stats postData=\r\n```\r\n\r\nare hanging (\"onResponse\" is missing) due to uknown web server issue (possibly not responding?). The web server is started once per whole `playwright:test` run, so it is valid that it isn't available for later tests (blank, white screen).\r\n\r\nWe need to understand why the web server stops responding. ",
